01:23 PM Defendant Chad L Conrath in court, in custody, with attorney Cassandra A Miller.   Atty Andrea M Will  and Intern, Alyssa Jay, appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Teuber appeared for the State on behalf of Jefferson County in Case 22CF525.
Victim rights have been complied with by the Waukesha County District Attorneys Office.
Case called for plea and sentencing in cases 22CF85, 22CF413, 22CF477, 22CF525, 22CF645, 22CF746, and 22CM72.
State places offer on the record.
Court conducts plea colloquy. 

Case 22CF525:
     Defendant enters a guilty plea to Counts 1 & 3.  Court finds defendant guilty.
     Count 2 is Dismissed and read in.

Case 22CF413:
     Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 2.  Court finds defendant guilty.
     Count 1 is Dismissed and read in.

Case 22CF746:
     Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.
     Count 2 is Dismissed and read in. 

Cases 22CM72, 22CF85, 22CF645, 22CF477 are Dismissed and Read in.
State and Defense make sentencing recommendations. 
Defendant makes statement to the court.

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:
Case 22CF413:
IMPOSED SENTENCE OF:

4  YEARS OF IMPRISONMENT (Credit:  0  Days)
2    YEARS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
2    YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION
Consecutive to:  Sentence currently being served. 

Defendant is not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is not eligible for Substance Abuse Program.  

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*Absolute Sobriety;  
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed;
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions;
*Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent; 
*Maintain full-time employment and/or combination of schooling;
*No contact with:  All victims across all cases; 
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done;
*No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed;
*Successful completion of Criminal Thinking course through the Department of Corrections;

COSTS:  $268     
DNA SAMPLE AND SURCHARGE:  $250     
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
**To be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision. 

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.

